# Jobs & Events

Use BullMQ for: email/SMS, payment webhook follow-up, media variants, search reindex, scheduled article publish, low-stock alerts, payout retries, analytics fan-out.

## Rules

- Handlers must be idempotent (at-least-once delivery)
- Explicit retry/backoff + dead-letter visibility
- Propagate correlation IDs
- Do not hide long external IO in request hot paths when a queue should own it
- Redis down must not corrupt money/inventory truth (DB remains source of record)

Example events: `OrderPaid`, `OrderCancelled`, `ArticlePublished`, `CampaignAwarded`, `DeliverableApproved`.
